Amanda Holden said her sister, Debbie, managed to contact family to say she was safe after a 7.9-magnitude earthquake struck Nepal on Saturday .
She said Debbie had not yet reached Everest Base Camp because she was ill and stopped off to recover .
The TV presenter said she had been able to send a text message to her family from a friend's phone to say that she had made it safely to base camp .
'We are extremely lucky. I'm dying to hear her voice,' she said .